\f3\b\fs28 Introduction
\f2\b0\fs24 \
\
	ChainShot is a simple puzzle game in which the object is to remove connected pieces of the same color such that the playing field is eventually cleared. It features multiple difficulty levels and board sizes to keep things interesting. ChainShot was originally an ASCII-based game released in 1985 by Kuniaki Moribe, and then introduced to the Mac as a desk accessory in 1992 by K&M Software. It has now been brought into the world of Mac OS X and Aqua so that future generations can also enjoy this addictive little game.\
