\f3\b\fs28 Usage
\f2\b0\fs24 \
\
	Start playing by clicking on connected pieces of the same color. They will be removed from the playing field, and the remaining ones will slide down and to the left, possibly setting up new connections. Repeat this until no moves are possible. The trick is to remove pieces in such a way as to bring previously isolated pieces in contact with other ones of the same color, such that they can be removed as well. Once you have completed a game, you can start a new one by clicking on the "Restart" button in the lower left corner. Immediately adjacent to it is a "Stats" button that lets you see your past performances on various difficulty and board size settings. These settings can be changed from the widget preferences dialog, accessible by control-clicking or right-clicking anywhere on the widget.\
